28 (B) has served not less than ten (10) years of the convicted
29 person's sentence.
30 (2) A convicted person who:
31 (A) is serving a sentence within the department of
32 correction for an offense that was committed when the
33 convicted person was at least twenty-six (26) years of age;
34 and
35 (B) has served not less than fifteen (15) years of the
36 convicted person's sentence.
37 (3) Any convicted person with the consent of the prosecuting
38 attorney.
39 The time periods described in this subsection are computed on the
